The current BART UI relies heavily on Experoâ€™s proprietary framework, which restricts customization, scalability, and long-term support. Many components are tightly coupled to vendor-specific code, making enhancements slow, costly, and difficult to maintain. The existing stack is outdated and misaligned with modern React best practices, limiting performance and developer productivity. Migrating to a modern React-based UI gives full control over the user experience, improves maintainability, and enables rapid feature development. It also allows adoption of advanced libraries like Cytoscape, MSAL, React Query, and TanStack Table for better performance and richer capabilities. Additionally, migration ensures seamless Azure SSO integration, stronger security, and eliminates vendor lock-in, reducing both future risks and operational costs.


